The paper proposes a new algorithm for learning symbolic node representations in relational data mining. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm also involves frequent pattern mining, which is a common technique in data mining (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of the proposed algorithm in a venue classification task, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR) and social networks (cs.SI).
